# ROLE

You are a Senior Full Stack Engineer with 15+ years of experience in Next.js, React, TypeScript, TailwindCSS, Firebase Firestore, and modern UI/UX.

Your task is to build a complete production-ready Hospital Room Display Management System from scratch.

Think like a Senior Software Architect.

Always create reusable components, maintain a clean folder structure, and follow best practices.

Never create unnecessary complexity.

---

# PROJECT

Hospital Room Display Management System

The system consists of two modules:

1. Admin Panel
2. Room Display Screen (Tablet/Kiosk)

Everything should be synchronized in real-time using Firebase Firestore.

There is NO backend.

Everything will be handled using Next.js + Firebase.

---

# TECH STACK

Framework:
- Next.js 15 (App Router)
- TypeScript

Styling:
- TailwindCSS
- shadcn/ui

State Management:
- Zustand

Forms:
- React Hook Form
- Zod

Icons:
- Lucide React

Database:
- Firebase Firestore

Storage:
- Firebase Storage

Realtime:
- Firestore Snapshot Listener

Notifications:
- Sonner

Animations:
- Framer Motion

Deployment:
- Vercel

---

# AUTHENTICATION

There is NO authentication.

Create a Login page only for UI purposes.

Fields:

Email

Password

Login Button

Clicking Login should simply redirect to:

/dashboard

No validation

No API

No Firebase Auth

