---

# ROUTES

/

Login Page

/dashboard

Dashboard

/rooms

Room Listing

/rooms/add

Add Room

/rooms/edit/[id]

Edit Room

/branding

Branding Settings

/audit

Audit Logs

/display/[roomId]

Public Tablet Display

---

# DASHBOARD

Create beautiful modern dashboard cards.

Show:

Total Rooms

Occupied Rooms

Vacant Rooms

Male Rooms

Female Rooms

Latest Updates

Quick Actions

---

# ROOM MODEL

interface Room {

id

roomNumber

roomName

department

floor

building

status

occupied | vacant

gender

male | female | null

displayUrl

createdAt

updatedAt

}

---

# ROOM MANAGEMENT

Admin can:

Create Room

Edit Room

Delete Room

Search Room

Filter Room

Copy Display URL

Generate Display URL automatically

Example:

/display/501

---

# DISPLAY SCREEN

The display will run on a tablet mounted outside the room.

The UI should look premium and modern.

Display:

Hospital Logo

Room Number

Room Name

Occupied/Vacant

Patient Gender

Current Time

Current Date

---

# DISPLAY STATES

If status == occupied

Header:

RED

Text:

OCCUPIED

Card:

Male

Blue

or

Female

Pink

LED side glow:

Red

--------------------------------

If status == vacant

Header:

GREEN

Text:

VACANT

Card:

Available

Green

No gender shown

LED side glow:

Green

---

# LOCAL TABLET CONTROLS

By default

Everything is LOCKED.

There should be a hidden floating button on the left or right side.

Click

↓

Open Unlock Dialog

↓

Pattern Lock Screen

↓

Success

↓

Open Settings Panel

---

# SETTINGS PANEL

Buttons

Occupied

Vacant

Male

Female

Save & Close

Cancel

---

# SAVE FLOW

Save

↓

Update Firestore

↓

Create Audit Log

↓

Refresh Admin Dashboard

↓

Refresh Every Tablet

↓

Close Panel

↓

Lock Again

---

# AUTO LOCK

Auto lock after 60 seconds of inactivity.

Configurable.

---

# BRANDING PAGE

Admin can upload:

Hospital Logo

Primary Color

Secondary Color

Every display should instantly update.

---

# AUDIT LOG

Every change should create a log.

Store:

timestamp

roomId

previousStatus

newStatus

previousGender

newGender

source

(Admin / Tablet)

Display logs inside a searchable table.

---

# FIREBASE COLLECTIONS

rooms

branding

auditLogs

Use Firestore best practices.

Create reusable services.

Do NOT access firestore directly inside components.

Use service layer.

Example

services/

room.service.ts

branding.service.ts

audit.service.ts

---

# UI DESIGN

Use modern enterprise design.

Rounded cards

Soft shadows

Responsive

Glass effect where appropriate

Smooth animations

Professional hospital appearance

Large typography

Accessible colors

Beautiful empty states

Skeleton loading

Toast notifications

---

# COMPONENTS

Everything must be reusable.

Button

Card

Modal

Dialog

StatusBadge

RoomCard

GenderCard

Header

Sidebar

DataTable

SearchInput

ColorPicker

LogoUploader

PatternLock

Clock

DateDisplay

---

# FIREBASE REALTIME

Every page should use realtime listeners.

If admin changes status

↓

Every display updates immediately.

If tablet changes status

↓

Dashboard updates immediately.

No refresh.

---

# RESPONSIVENESS

Desktop

Tablet

Landscape Tablet

Mobile

Support fullscreen kiosk mode.

---

# CODE QUALITY

Use TypeScript everywhere.

No any types.

Use reusable hooks.

Separate business logic.

No duplicated code.

Follow SOLID principles.

Keep components under 200 lines.

Use constants instead of magic strings.

---

# PERFORMANCE

Use Server Components where possible.

Use Client Components only when necessary.

Optimize rerenders.

Lazy load heavy components.

Memoize expensive calculations.

---

# ERROR HANDLING

Empty state

Loading state

Error state

Offline state

No data state

---

# FUTURE READY

Architecture should allow adding:

Multi Hospital

Multiple Admins

Arabic Language

QR Code

Emergency Broadcast

Device Monitoring

Analytics

Without major refactoring.

---

# EXPECTATIONS

Before generating code:

1. Plan folder structure
2. Plan Firebase schema
3. Plan reusable components
4. Plan services
5. Plan hooks
6. Plan UI
7. Plan routing

After planning,

Generate the project step by step.

Never generate placeholder code if real implementation can be created.

Always generate production-ready code.

Always explain file structure before creating files.

Always keep consistency across the entire project.

Act as a Senior Engineer, UI Designer, and Software Architect simultaneously.